<li class="comment byuser comment-author-mcrustawildernesscat-com bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-61157">
<article id="comment-61157" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='small mallory photo' src='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-44x44.jpg' srcset='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-88x88.jpg 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn"><a href='https://www.wildernesscat.com/' rel='external nofollow ugc' class='url'>Mallory Crusta</a></b> <span>Post author</span></cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/best-cat-water-fountain#comment-61157"><time datetime="2021-10-03T17:33:43+00:00">Oct 3, 2021 at 5:33 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Hi Janet, apologies for the late reply, and thank you for commenting. I&#8217;ve switched out the links so they now direct users to the $33 listing from Petkit. As for the Petkit Eversweet Solo, the biggest difference besides size is that the Solo doesn&#8217;t have a night mode, so the water will always work in 3-minute intervals every 5 minutes, while the Petkit Eversweet 2 will automatically reduce its recirculation periods to 3 minutes every hour. Additionally, the Solo is a little bit quieter than the Eversweet 2, producing about 30 db in contrast to the Eversweet 2&#8217;s operating noise of 40 db. You can learn more about the differences between various Petkit water fountain models here: <a href="https://petkit.id/EVERSWEET-SOLO.pdf" rel="nofollow ugc">https://petkit.id/EVERSWEET-SOLO.pdf</a></p>
</section>
