<article id="comment-82822" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0722870c85ef96a82a53ac6eb1492030?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0722870c85ef96a82a53ac6eb1492030?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Stephanie Barnard</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/best-cat-water-fountain#comment-82822"><time datetime="2022-06-12T19:29:32+00:00">Jun 12, 2022 at 7:29 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>This is my favorite cat fountain thirstycatfountains.com. I know they are a little pricey, but they are beautiful and you won&#8217;t mind putting them anywhere there is an outlet. Ceramic, made in the USA. Each one is unique. I have two of them. They are very easy to clean and all 4 of my cats use them daily. The water is horrible in my town, so I always use &#8220;Zero Water&#8221; filtered water. I&#8217;ve had both for over 10 years. I have a cat who likes to push her water bowl across the floor to watch the water slosh out. These are so heavy, she can&#8217;t move them at all. She is the reason I bought the first one.</p>
</section>
