<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Hello, I love this review and appreciate the resource very much! One thing I do wish was included in the reviews are a bit more about the filter cartridges. I’ve noticed quite a few pet fountains have filter cartridges with plastic parts. I am not a fan of disposable plastic so one of my most essential criteria for a fountain is that the filters have zero plastic pieces and are simple filter media whatever it may be. I know the Npet Catit and drinkwell have no plastic in the filter cartridges but it would be nice to know more about all of them incase I’m missing anything.</p>
</section>
